.NET Framework 3.5.name: OVRGrabbable
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: An object that can be grabbed and thrown by OVRGrabber.

methods.name: GrabBegin(OVRGrabber hand, Collider grabPoint)
methods.summary: Notifies the object that it has been grabbed.
methods.syntax: public virtual void GrabBegin(OVRGrabber hand, Collider grabPoint)
methods.linkedSyntax: public virtual void GrabBegin([OVRGrabber](#/type/GlobalNamespace.OVRGrabber/index) hand, Collider grabPoint)

methods.name: GrabEnd(Vector3 linearVelocity, Vector3 angularVelocity)
methods.summary: Notifies the object that it has been released.
methods.syntax: public virtual void GrabEnd(Vector3 linearVelocity, Vector3 angularVelocity)
methods.linkedSyntax: public virtual void GrabEnd(Vector3 linearVelocity, Vector3 angularVelocity)

properties.name: allowOffhandGrab
properties.summary: If true, the object can currently be grabbed.

properties.name: grabbedBy
properties.summary: Returns the OVRGrabber currently grabbing this object.

properties.name: grabbedRigidbody
properties.summary: The Rigidbody of the collider that was used to grab this object.

properties.name: grabbedTransform
properties.summary: The transform at which this object was grabbed.

properties.name: grabPoints
properties.summary: The contact point(s) where the object was grabbed.

properties.name: isGrabbed
properties.summary: If true, the object is currently grabbed.

properties.name: snapOffset
properties.summary: An offset relative to the OVRGrabber where this object can snap when grabbed.

properties.name: snapOrientation
properties.summary: If true, the object's orientation will snap to match snapOffset when grabbed.

properties.name: snapPosition
properties.summary: If true, the object's position will snap to match snapOffset when grabbed.
